						<summary>

						<p>The inscription is mutilated at the beginning and is also incomplete. Hence the object of the record is not known. The details of the date are given as Dhanus, ba. 9, Sunday, A[śvini] or A[ttam] which would correspond to A.D. 1162, December 2. The nakshatra was Hasta on this date.</p>						

						<p>Mention is made of Rājanārāyaṇanallūr the eastern area of Iraiyānaraiyūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻakēraḷa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Pāṉūr-kūṟṟam, a division of Malāḍu <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Jananātha-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
